263
00:20:03,768 --> 00:20:05,048
Like him, my arse

264
00:20:05,048 --> 00:20:06,022
(Bell sound)

265
00:20:06,982 --> 00:20:08,648
I gotta go.

266
00:20:08,648 --> 00:20:09,668
Okay. Bye.

267
00:20:15,805 --> 00:20:16,650
Ouch!

268
00:20:23,782 --> 00:20:24,768
(Bell sound)

269
00:20:29,896 --> 00:20:30,650
(Sound of door opening)

270
00:20:31,999 --> 00:20:33,268
Hi, doc.

271
00:20:42,525 --> 00:20:43,485
It’s ready, Tharn.

272
00:20:46,856 --> 00:20:47,976
Boiled rice, fresh from the oven.

273
00:20:48,948 --> 00:20:50,399
Let me do that.

274
00:20:50,490 --> 00:20:52,193
Eat with while it’s still hot.

275
00:20:52,216 --> 00:20:53,096
So that you’d feel better from the hangover.

276
00:20:53,759 --> 00:20:54,559
Thank you.

277
00:21:17,816 --> 00:21:19,039
Is everything all right?

278
00:21:19,508 --> 00:21:20,582
Does it taste that bad?

279
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:24,216
Oh no. It’s really good.

280
00:21:25,942 --> 00:21:29,039
The food you buy for me always tastes really good.

281
00:21:30,536 --> 00:21:31,508
Thank you so much.

282
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:32,456
And...

283
00:21:33,165 --> 00:21:34,856
thank you about last night too.

284
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:39,016
Tharn.

285
00:21:40,936 --> 00:21:43,528
Who’s that friend who was looking after you last night?

286
00:21:43,965 --> 00:21:45,058
I’ve never seen him before.

287
00:21:46,159 --> 00:21:49,439
His name is Phaya. He’s my friend at the unit.

288
00:21:50,428 --> 00:21:54,982
Seems like you two are quite close, aren’t you?

289
00:21:55,930 --> 00:21:57,938
Because last night I noticed that.

290
00:21:57,938 --> 00:21:59,553
He was really worried about you.

291
00:22:01,268 --> 00:22:02,856
Not that close.

292
00:22:03,439 --> 00:22:06,159
He just likes to annoy me and get on my nerve.

293
00:22:08,525 --> 00:22:09,782
Go on and finish your food.

294
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:10,913
Then I’ll drop you off.

295
00:22:13,450 --> 00:22:14,058
What!

296
00:22:15,565 --> 00:22:17,199
Drop me off? Do I have to go somewhere?

297
00:22:17,348 --> 00:22:20,456
Did you forget that you have to fly to Nongkai today?

298
00:22:20,479 --> 00:22:21,839
Oh, that’s right!

299
00:22:22,925 --> 00:22:25,308
If you hadn’t remind me then I’d have missed the flight for sure.

300
00:22:25,308 --> 00:22:26,548
Go pack your things then.

301
00:22:27,165 --> 00:22:27,988
Yai!

302
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:31,538
Wake up right now!

303
00:22:31,538 --> 00:22:33,462
Did you forget that you have to go to Nongkai?

304
00:22:35,928 --> 00:22:40,088
Nongkai.

305
00:23:24,639 --> 00:23:25,622
Look at her.

306
00:23:27,096 --> 00:23:29,688
She was giving me all ears while we were on the plane.

307
00:23:29,793 --> 00:23:31,848
She’s still mad with me.

308
00:23:32,319 --> 00:23:33,408
So, my dear brother.

309
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,168
Help me make up with her.

310
00:23:35,588 --> 00:23:39,210
Or else I’d be cleaning the toilet at home during the festival this evening.

311
00:23:41,428 --> 00:23:42,673
Seriously…

312
00:23:43,128 --> 00:23:46,593
Sand isn’t that kind of girl. She’ll forgive you soon enough.

313
00:23:46,608 --> 00:23:48,285
Before you said that...

314
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:49,828
make sure you look at her face first.

315
00:23:59,759 --> 00:24:01,108
She’s gorgeous.

316
00:24:02,719 --> 00:24:08,048
I know that. But she’s also very scary. I’m afraid of her.

317
00:24:08,058 --> 00:24:09,428
Are you guys talking about me?

318
00:24:10,488 --> 00:24:11,805
Of course, not.

319
00:24:12,296 --> 00:24:14,668
He was telling me how nice you are.

320
00:24:15,096 --> 00:24:17,530
And that you look really beautiful today.

321
00:24:18,399 --> 00:24:20,728
But you’d look even more beautiful...

322
00:24:20,728 --> 00:24:22,788
if you stop being mad at him.

323
00:24:22,788 --> 00:24:25,448
Incredibly beautiful, my baby.

324
00:24:25,448 --> 00:24:27,448
Do you want some water? The weathe is quite hot.

325
00:24:27,448 --> 00:24:29,553
But you look even hotter.

326
00:24:30,056 --> 00:24:31,798
Tonight at the festival...

327
00:24:31,798 --> 00:24:33,768
should we go try something delicious?

328
00:24:33,768 --> 00:24:34,102
Okay.

329
00:24:34,102 --> 00:24:36,008
Like Spicy Papaya Salad...

330
00:24:36,368 --> 00:24:39,948
And grilled river fish with chilled beer.

331
00:24:41,199 --> 00:24:42,628
My mouth is watering just by thinking of them.

332
00:24:42,776 --> 00:24:43,888
How would you like that, honey?

333
00:24:43,888 --> 00:24:46,525
Yes, I really love chilled beer.

334
00:24:46,673 --> 00:24:50,528
Those are all your favourites, huh?

335
00:24:50,988 --> 00:24:52,536
I still haven’t lectured you about last night.

336
00:24:52,536 --> 00:24:56,128
That you got so drunk and almost made us both miss the plane.

337
00:24:57,199 --> 00:24:59,038
Oh, so you remembered? Why didn’t you tell me then?

338
00:24:59,038 --> 00:25:01,228
Are you blaming me now?

339
00:25:01,798 --> 00:25:02,738
Is it my fault?

340
00:25:02,738 --> 00:25:06,278
What? Of course, not, sweetie.

341
00:25:06,278 --> 00:25:10,358
I was just kidding. Please forgive me. It’s all my fault.

342
00:25:10,358 --> 00:25:14,758
It’s my fault. Please tell me what you want me to do tonight, my baby.

343
00:25:14,758 --> 00:25:16,478
Please behave. We’re at the temple.

344
00:25:16,478 --> 00:25:18,102
Let’s go see the Abbot.

345
00:25:20,296 --> 00:25:22,848
Honey, wait for me too. Don’t you want some water?

346
00:25:22,848 --> 00:25:24,856
I bought it from over there.

347
00:25:26,662 --> 00:25:29,188
Isn’t she adorable? That’s my wife.

348
00:25:30,502 --> 00:25:32,038
Goodmorning, Luangpor.

349
00:25:32,038 --> 00:25:34,068
Morning.

350
00:25:35,439 --> 00:25:39,848
Come a little closer. I’m happy for you two.

351
00:25:40,428 --> 00:25:45,698
You’re now on the special investigation team just like what you’ve wanted to.

352
00:25:46,228 --> 00:25:49,199
It’s all because of you, Luangpor,

353
00:25:49,218 --> 00:25:51,050
that we could finally did it.

354
00:25:51,298 --> 00:25:53,988
You’ve always taken a great care of us.

355
00:25:53,988 --> 00:25:55,176
We are who we are because of you.

356
00:25:55,919 --> 00:25:58,045
We are so grateful to you.

357
00:26:00,198 --> 00:26:04,673
You did it because you already have it in you.

358
00:26:05,336 --> 00:26:07,965
Please take a good care of yourself from now on.

359
00:26:08,410 --> 00:26:10,616
Be mindful in everything you do.

360
00:26:11,688 --> 00:26:13,508
Never lose your awareness.

361
00:26:14,010 --> 00:26:15,028
Always be calm.

362
00:26:15,628 --> 00:26:16,650
Don’t be a hotheaded.

363
00:26:17,968 --> 00:26:20,753
As long as he has me with him, I’ll always make sure he behaves.

364
00:26:22,558 --> 00:26:23,782
I’ll always make sure he behaves.

365
00:26:23,782 --> 00:26:25,778
You can rest assured that he’ll always be mindful.

366
00:26:27,868 --> 00:26:30,902
Maybe you should tell that to yourself first.

367
00:26:31,690 --> 00:26:34,765
Whenever they are together, there’s always trouble.

368
00:26:35,736 --> 00:26:36,833
I agree.

369
00:26:37,073 --> 00:26:38,582
Totally agree.

370
00:26:39,256 --> 00:26:41,542
Without you...

371
00:26:42,118 --> 00:26:44,845
harn would surely be more calm and always think twice.

372
00:26:45,256 --> 00:26:47,788
You are quick-tempered and act on impluse.

373
00:26:47,788 --> 00:26:50,570
Please mercy me.

374
00:26:51,038 --> 00:26:53,268
Darling, I got scolded again.

375
00:26:53,268 --> 00:26:53,728
There you go.

376
00:26:53,728 --> 00:26:56,308
Ouch! It really hurts, babe.

377
00:26:56,308 --> 00:26:57,378
Does it?

378
00:26:57,378 --> 00:26:58,168
Does it hurt a lot?

379
00:26:58,168 --> 00:26:59,256
Ouch!….

380
00:27:00,148 --> 00:27:01,736
Go that way.

381
00:27:02,388 --> 00:27:05,408
While you’re staying here.

382
00:27:05,736 --> 00:27:07,668
Let me warn you about something

383
00:27:08,479 --> 00:27:12,765
Make sure you often meditate and dedicate the merits to those whom you have wronged in the past.

384
00:27:14,056 --> 00:27:17,782
So that it would help lighten the consequences of your karma.

385
00:27:17,798 --> 00:27:18,833
Got it?

386
00:27:23,108 --> 00:27:25,668
Is he still not free from them?

387
00:27:25,965 --> 00:27:27,628
They’ve been after him since when he was born.

388
00:27:28,010 --> 00:27:29,816
That’s why he had to live at the temple.

389
00:27:30,308 --> 00:27:33,519
What do they want from him? Why are they so vengeful?

390
00:27:59,576 --> 00:28:02,388
Are you going to Rocket Festival tonight?

391
00:28:03,153 --> 00:28:05,318
Absolutely. They won’t miss the chance.

392
00:28:06,399 --> 00:28:08,765
Do you want to go home to visit your grandma first?

393
00:28:08,879 --> 00:28:10,925
We can meet again this evening.

394
00:28:12,288 --> 00:28:14,342
’m going to stay here tonight.

395
00:28:14,498 --> 00:28:17,142
So that I can help take care of the Abbot.

396
00:28:17,782 --> 00:28:19,758
You and Yai go back first.

397
00:28:20,079 --> 00:28:21,199
I’ll give you a call later.

398
00:28:21,542 --> 00:28:22,376
Okay.

399
00:28:23,658 --> 00:28:25,919
We’d get going then. Goodbye, Luangpor.

400
00:28:25,942 --> 00:28:28,170
Stay safe, both of you.

401
00:28:36,422 --> 00:28:40,479
Tharn, can you do me a favour?

402
00:28:41,793 --> 00:28:42,788
Luangpor,

403
00:28:43,393 --> 00:28:46,022
Why do you ask me to bring an extra set of bedding?

404
00:28:46,239 --> 00:28:48,536
Someone will also sleep here tonight.

405
00:28:49,038 --> 00:28:52,348
Go and make your bed in the pavillioin first.

406
00:28:52,353 --> 00:28:53,508
Okay.

407
00:28:58,502 --> 00:29:00,422
Phaya!

408
00:29:01,713 --> 00:29:03,656
Tharn!

409
00:29:04,559 --> 00:29:05,588
What on earth are you doing here?

410
00:29:15,393 --> 00:29:18,168
Goodevening, Luangpor. Do you remember me?

411
00:29:19,085 --> 00:29:22,968
Oh, I haven’t seen you for a long time. How are you?

412
00:29:23,668 --> 00:29:24,708
I’m good.

413
00:29:25,119 --> 00:29:29,210
You two spent a lot of time together during the training, didn’t you recognised each other?

414
00:29:32,136 --> 00:29:35,382
Do you mean, Phaya and I...

415
00:29:35,702 --> 00:29:38,193
have met before we went to the training camp?

416
00:29:38,868 --> 00:29:40,285
That’s right.

417
00:29:40,508 --> 00:29:46,296
You used to give him the amulet when he was young.

418
00:29:46,536 --> 00:29:47,393
What?

419
00:29:50,662 --> 00:29:52,799
You’re that boy who gave me the amulet?

420
00:30:10,948 --> 00:30:13,313
Thank you so much, Luangpor.

421
00:30:13,999 --> 00:30:17,805
For always taking care of Tharn since the day he lost his parents in an accident.

422
00:30:17,999 --> 00:30:19,888
You and this temple...

423
00:30:19,888 --> 00:30:22,228
have always been a sanctuary for Tharn and I.

424
00:30:25,388 --> 00:30:30,548
He often told me that all he has is his grandmother.

425
00:30:30,959 --> 00:30:34,113
So, he doesn’t want anything bad to happen to you.

426
00:30:34,658 --> 00:30:37,039
That’s why he asked if he could live here.

427
00:30:40,061 --> 00:30:43,161
I don’t want him to blame himself.

428
00:30:44,102 --> 00:30:45,428
I could only hope that...

429
00:30:45,679 --> 00:30:50,488
he will eventually forget about that terrible accident when he gets older.

430
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:54,582
Everything has already been destined.

431
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:58,959
His life is written by the karma he did in his past life.

432
00:31:00,788 --> 00:31:02,868
Is there a way to fix it?

433
00:31:06,422 --> 00:31:07,679
Well, there is somehow.

434
00:31:08,753 --> 00:31:16,079
His destiny has been entwined with someone since his past life.

435
00:31:16,639 --> 00:31:20,970
That person will lead him to experience bad things.

436
00:31:22,193 --> 00:31:28,022
But it is also that person who would be able to free him from his karma.

437
00:31:51,016 --> 00:31:52,788
Tharn, let’s go to the festival.

438
00:31:54,728 --> 00:32:00,845
Tharn, it’s the 15th day of the 11th waxing moon today. Are you going to the Rocket Festival with Yai?

439
00:32:01,039 --> 00:32:02,125
Yes, grandma.

440
00:32:02,422 --> 00:32:03,988
Please don’t worry.

441
00:32:04,018 --> 00:32:05,698
I’ll take a good care of myself.

442
00:32:05,698 --> 00:32:08,170
When the festival is done, I’ll go visit you at home.

443
00:32:10,170 --> 00:32:11,408
Take care of each other, okay?

444
00:32:11,408 --> 00:32:12,010
Yes, grandma.

445
00:32:13,165 --> 00:32:14,513
- Let's help pack up
- Okay.

446
00:32:16,978 --> 00:32:21,976
Tharn, I need a little favour from you.

447
00:32:23,558 --> 00:32:28,982
Make sure you track down the owner of this amulet by tonight.

448
00:32:30,033 --> 00:32:32,936
Once you’ve found him, give him this amulet.

449
00:32:37,245 --> 00:32:41,119
Who is the owner of this amulet, Luangpor?

450
00:32:42,125 --> 00:32:46,348
If you meet him, your feelings will tell you.

451
00:32:46,348 --> 00:32:48,582
Who is the owner of this necklace?

452
00:32:49,016 --> 00:32:51,233
But you must find him.

453
00:32:51,778 --> 00:32:55,576
Whether you’d be free from those whom you have wronged in the past...

454
00:32:56,365 --> 00:33:02,056
depends on whether you’d be able to find the owner of this amulet tonight.

455
00:33:09,245 --> 00:33:10,388
Let’s go.

456
00:33:11,050 --> 00:33:12,193
Goodbye, Luangpor.

457
00:33:15,948 --> 00:33:20,125
Tharn! Yai! Come quick! What took you so long? I’ve been here for a while.

458
00:33:20,719 --> 00:33:22,045
Let’s go.

459
00:33:39,618 --> 00:33:42,708
Who are you looking for?

460
00:33:43,096 --> 00:33:46,136
The person that the Abbot asked me to give this amulet to.

461
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:50,890
Geez, I thought you and I could just have fun at the festival.

462
00:33:51,176 --> 00:33:54,730
Too bad the Abbot also gave you a mission for tonight.

463
00:33:55,370 --> 00:33:56,650
Now, I’m bored.

464
00:33:57,348 --> 00:34:02,328
The Abbot said there’ll be a sign and I’ll know once I see him.

465
00:34:02,559 --> 00:34:04,445
The owner of this amulet.

466
00:34:04,458 --> 00:34:06,228
What sign?

467
00:34:06,228 --> 00:34:08,061
What are you two talking about?

468
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:10,662
Some nonsese stuff.

469
00:34:12,348 --> 00:34:14,548
Let’s light up these firecrackers. I bought tons of them.

470
00:34:14,548 --> 00:34:18,113
After we finish eating, let’s go watch something at the outdoor cinema.

471
00:34:18,193 --> 00:34:19,256
Yeah, let’s do that.

472
00:34:19,258 --> 00:34:20,719
- You take the meatballs to eat first.
- Okay

473
00:34:21,393 --> 00:34:23,142
What’s this for?

474
00:34:25,028 --> 00:34:28,208
Help! Help! My nephew is drowning!

475
00:34:30,308 --> 00:34:32,528
Help! My nephew is drowning!

476
00:34:41,588 --> 00:34:44,448
Tharn, what’s wrong?

477
00:34:45,999 --> 00:34:48,148
I saw a boy drowning.

478
00:34:48,178 --> 00:34:50,318
Geez, nonsense.

479
00:34:50,318 --> 00:34:52,182
Are you going to tell me that you have a vision?

480
00:34:52,688 --> 00:34:53,788
But I really saw it.

481
00:34:53,788 --> 00:34:56,288
Nonsense. Let’s go watch a movie.

482
00:34:56,288 --> 00:34:58,262
Help! My nephew is drowning!

483
00:35:05,998 --> 00:35:09,688
Help! Help! My nephew is drowning!

484
00:35:09,688 --> 00:35:13,496
Help! My nephew! He is drowning!

485
00:35:28,239 --> 00:35:29,142
Phaya!

486
00:35:30,650 --> 00:35:31,828
Phaya!

487
00:35:37,382 --> 00:35:38,456
Phaya!

488
00:35:41,965 --> 00:35:42,833
Wake up

489
00:35:45,688 --> 00:35:47,519
- Wake up
- Phaya

490
00:35:47,588 --> 00:35:49,528
- Wake up
- Phaya

491
00:35:49,528 --> 00:35:50,528
(Choke)

492
00:35:57,519 --> 00:35:59,599
(Crying sound)

493
00:36:09,858 --> 00:36:10,502
Thank you

494
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:13,008
It’s okay. You’re safe now.

495
00:36:32,662 --> 00:36:35,538
Here are your clothes. Let’s go and get changed.

496
00:36:35,538 --> 00:36:41,073
- Thank you all of you so much for saving his life.
- You’re welcome.

497
00:36:43,199 --> 00:36:44,182
Tharn.

498
00:36:44,658 --> 00:36:46,490
You should go and get changed too.

499
00:36:47,688 --> 00:36:49,028
We’d get going then.

500
00:36:49,245 --> 00:36:50,678
Goodbye.

501
00:37:03,058 --> 00:37:06,878
Without him, my nephew would have been dead.

502
00:37:06,878 --> 00:37:08,608
Thank you so much indeed.

503
00:37:08,608 --> 00:37:13,279
Oh, it’s all right. I was quite worried when I heard about it.

504
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:16,250
But what a relief to know that they were all safe.

505
00:37:17,656 --> 00:37:20,445
It’s probably like what you said.

506
00:37:21,610 --> 00:37:24,888
Your nephew is a very fortunate boy.

507
00:37:24,888 --> 00:37:26,673
So, he would probably live for a very long time.

508
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:29,713
But you have to be careful though.

509
00:37:30,970 --> 00:37:35,610
If both of your destiny are entwined like what I think...

510
00:37:36,993 --> 00:37:40,205
you would eventually find each other again.

511
00:37:44,658 --> 00:37:48,822
Please take this as a thank you gift for saving my nephew’s life.

512
00:37:49,478 --> 00:37:55,016
Thank you, ma’am. But my grandma and the Abbot have taught me to always help those who are in need.

513
00:37:55,038 --> 00:37:58,102
Hey, but you did something good so you should take it.

514
00:38:00,136 --> 00:38:01,608
I’ll take it then.

515
00:38:01,608 --> 00:38:02,398
Thank you.

516
00:38:02,398 --> 00:38:03,245
Ouch!

517
00:38:06,438 --> 00:38:11,302
Well, then...I’ll give it to the Abbot instead.

518
00:38:12,118 --> 00:38:17,638
I’d like to donate this money for the temple and those who live here.

519
00:38:17,638 --> 00:38:20,845
So that you could use it as an education fund of these kids.

520
00:38:24,879 --> 00:38:27,793
I'm so close to getting the money,The Abbot.

