01:00:51,257 --> 01:00:52,675
There’s more. Let’s go.

788
01:00:52,885 --> 01:00:54,126
- Is there anything else?
- There is more to come.

789
01:01:00,103 --> 01:01:01,520
Do you like it?

790
01:01:01,737 --> 01:01:02,549
Incredible.

791
01:01:04,343 --> 01:01:05,200
Any more places like this?

792
01:01:06,492 --> 01:01:07,383
You want to see more?

793
01:01:08,766 --> 01:01:09,863
Wait.

794
01:01:11,932 --> 01:01:12,595
What is it?

795
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:16,949
If you want to freshen up, have it with this.

796
01:01:21,189 --> 01:01:21,955
Thanks.

797
01:01:22,183 --> 01:01:23,806
I’m going to find something to eat. So hungry right now.

798
01:01:36,915 --> 01:01:38,389
Try this and you’ll feel fresh.

799
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:47,852
Do you think I can drink it now?

800
01:01:48,240 --> 01:01:49,155
Yeah.

801
01:01:55,806 --> 01:01:56,663
Ah, so fresh.

802
01:01:56,655 --> 01:01:58,320
Here, try it.

803
01:01:59,326 --> 01:02:01,212
Why would you put the cap on?

804
01:02:03,303 --> 01:02:04,229
By the way,

805
01:02:04,869 --> 01:02:06,343
I had a bad dream again last night.

806
01:02:08,355 --> 01:02:09,657
Again?

807
01:02:09,675 --> 01:02:10,423
Yeah.

808
01:02:13,177 --> 01:02:14,103
What was it like?

809
01:02:14,812 --> 01:02:20,595
Same old story. But this time, you were there in my dream too.

810
01:02:22,640 --> 01:02:24,229
Are you saying it was because of me

811
01:02:24,343 --> 01:02:25,417
that you had a bad dream?

812
01:02:26,652 --> 01:02:30,972
Of course, not. Forget it. Let’s go then.

813
01:02:32,297 --> 01:02:33,383
Where to, next?

814
01:02:34,815 --> 01:02:38,695
Wat Hai Sok (Nongkai province)

815
01:03:07,372 --> 01:03:09,532
Wow, is this your house?

816
01:03:09,783 --> 01:03:12,595
It looks really classy.

817
01:03:13,045 --> 01:03:16,012
I thought you said you grew up with the Abbot at the temple.

818
01:03:17,269 --> 01:03:19,029
This is my grandma’s place.

819
01:03:19,372 --> 01:03:21,383
I often come to visit her.

820
01:03:22,195 --> 01:03:27,175
Why didn’t you stay here then? The house is big. Why did you have to trouble the Abbot?

821
01:03:28,743 --> 01:03:31,417
I have my own reason which I don’t have to tell you.

822
01:03:32,855 --> 01:03:37,943
- But if you keep pesterting, I’d say you’re being rude.
- He means you’re nosy.

823
01:03:37,935 --> 01:03:40,366
Guys,

824
01:03:40,495 --> 01:03:43,246
please watch your mouth. We’re at his grandma’s place

825
01:03:43,245 --> 01:03:44,137
Not your own home.

826
01:03:45,425 --> 01:03:47,932
Like you’d let me talk like that in my own home.

827
01:03:48,389 --> 01:03:50,995
You knew that too? But you hardly do what I ask you to do though.

828
01:03:51,257 --> 01:03:51,886
Sorry

829
01:03:51,885 --> 01:03:55,695
Welcome home. You’ve arrived in time for dinner.

830
01:03:55,715 --> 01:03:57,772
I’ve prepared a feast for all of you.

831
01:03:58,295 --> 01:03:59,829
Hello, grandma.

832
01:03:59,825 --> 01:04:01,657
Hello.

833
01:04:02,057 --> 01:04:03,760
I miss you so much.

834
01:04:05,109 --> 01:04:05,669
Really?

835
01:04:07,097 --> 01:04:09,749
I’m sorry I didn’t call you that often.

836
01:04:10,085 --> 01:04:13,269
The instructors at the camp was very strict about us using our phones.

837
01:04:13,855 --> 01:04:14,766
So, I....

838
01:04:14,935 --> 01:04:17,212
completely forgot about me?

839
01:04:19,349 --> 01:04:20,755
Grandma.

840
01:04:20,755 --> 01:04:24,320
He was right. It was very strict there.

841
01:04:24,335 --> 01:04:27,212
I could hardly find a time to call my girlfriend.

842
01:04:27,225 --> 01:04:29,132
Because I had to call my mistress no.1,

843
01:04:29,125 --> 01:04:31,189
no.2 and then no.3 first.

844
01:04:31,185 --> 01:04:32,183
By the time I had to call Sand,

845
01:04:32,175 --> 01:04:34,172
my break time was over.

846
01:04:34,926 --> 01:04:36,137
Is that so? You rascal.

847
01:04:36,135 --> 01:04:38,400
Ouch!

848
01:04:40,229 --> 01:04:42,160
Didn’t you just tell us to watch our mouths while we are here?

849
01:04:42,686 --> 01:04:44,720
How dare you cursed in front of her like that.

850
01:04:44,972 --> 01:04:47,040
You’re a bad girl.

851
01:04:47,035 --> 01:04:48,252
Look at him, grandma.

852
01:04:48,366 --> 01:04:50,297
Why didn’t you say anything to defend me?

853
01:04:50,295 --> 01:04:51,749
Why should I?

854
01:04:51,886 --> 01:04:55,966
I was actually going to ask her to do it on another side too.

855
01:04:55,965 --> 01:04:57,052
- Another side?
- You got it.

856
01:04:57,045 --> 01:04:57,715
On this side.

857
01:04:57,715 --> 01:05:00,595
Hold on. She was just kidding.

858
01:05:00,629 --> 01:05:01,886
She really meant it.

859
01:05:04,875 --> 01:05:07,006
Is this your new friend?

860
01:05:08,183 --> 01:05:10,069
Why does he look so familiar?

861
01:05:11,120 --> 01:05:12,240
Hello, grandma.

862
01:05:13,235 --> 01:05:16,480
I’m the boy who almost got drowned, the one that Tharn had rescused on that day.

863
01:05:18,160 --> 01:05:18,857
Huh?

864
01:05:20,515 --> 01:05:24,057
Oh my goodness. It’s really you.

865
01:05:24,183 --> 01:05:27,825
I wouldn’t be able to recognise you if you hadn’t told me so.

866
01:05:27,825 --> 01:05:29,680
It’s such a coincidence.

867
01:05:29,675 --> 01:05:31,863
that we finally meet again after that day.

868
01:05:32,423 --> 01:05:34,069
After over a decade,

869
01:05:34,217 --> 01:05:36,697
we finally met again at the training camp.

870
01:05:38,766 --> 01:05:39,589
Yes,

871
01:05:40,815 --> 01:05:42,880
what a coincidence. Fascinating indeed.

872
01:05:45,509 --> 01:05:46,949
Are you all right, grandma?

873
01:05:47,715 --> 01:05:49,086
I’m okay.

874
01:05:50,172 --> 01:05:51,840
Welcome, all of you.

875
01:05:53,932 --> 01:05:54,629
Let’s go inside.

876
01:05:54,846 --> 01:05:56,625
You all must be famished.

877
01:05:57,166 --> 01:06:00,320
Let’s eat while the food is still hot.

878
01:06:01,035 --> 01:06:02,480
Let’s go then.

879
01:06:02,475 --> 01:06:03,349
Let’s go.

880
01:06:04,492 --> 01:06:07,840
Darling, that area where you pinched me hurts.

881
01:06:22,315 --> 01:06:25,760
French people do this to say hi and goodbye.

882
01:06:25,755 --> 01:06:26,857
Can I go to sleep now?

883
01:06:30,375 --> 01:06:37,335
The Sign
MingErTeamSub
Eng Trans @ThesignIDF

884
01:06:37,454 --> 01:06:44,434
The Sign

885
01:06:47,065 --> 01:06:49,305
So, what are you and Phaya?

886
01:06:51,065 --> 01:06:52,505
What do you mean?

887
01:06:53,979 --> 01:06:59,305
I can tell, you know? Your eyes just say it all.

888
01:07:01,351 --> 01:07:02,996
We’re just colleagues.

889
01:07:03,499 --> 01:07:06,368
- Hmm, colleagues? / - Yeah.

890
01:07:06,594 --> 01:07:11,225
But Yai told me that while you were at the camp,

891
01:07:11,842 --> 01:07:14,356
you were quite worried about Phaya.

892
01:07:14,574 --> 01:07:16,299
That you cared about him a lot.

893
01:07:16,596 --> 01:07:19,351
Probably a lot more than friends do.

894
01:07:22,299 --> 01:07:24,265
Haven’t I told you...

895
01:07:25,214 --> 01:07:26,802
that I don’t want to feel hurt like that anymore?

896
01:07:27,654 --> 01:07:31,934
Why? Is it because he’s a guy?

897
01:07:32,284 --> 01:07:34,825
Look at me and Yai.

898
01:07:34,844 --> 01:07:39,214
I don’t give a damn on what other people say about us.

899
01:07:39,614 --> 01:07:45,671
So, no matter how crazy or how annoying he is...

900
01:07:46,334 --> 01:07:47,739
I still love him.

901
01:07:51,111 --> 01:07:53,248
It’s not what you think.

902
01:07:54,344 --> 01:08:00,584
Be honest. If you like him, just admit it.

903
01:08:00,699 --> 01:08:03,088
Just tell him how you actually feel.

904
01:08:03,339 --> 01:08:07,234
Why do you have to complicate things?

905
01:08:07,254 --> 01:08:08,459
Just be a man and say it.

906
01:08:09,876 --> 01:08:18,074
I don’t want to put those around me in danger.

907
01:08:19,494 --> 01:08:23,374
Geez, you should stop blaming yourself.

908
01:08:25,648 --> 01:08:27,644
Your parents’ death was an accident.

909
01:08:27,854 --> 01:08:29,556
It wasn’t because of you.

910
01:08:30,544 --> 01:08:35,259
If what you said is true, Yai and I both love you like our own brother...

911
01:08:35,274 --> 01:08:37,305
but we’re still safe and sound.

912
01:08:39,774 --> 01:08:42,094
It would only happen to the one I love.

913
01:08:44,951 --> 01:08:46,619
It has always been like that.

914
01:08:47,814 --> 01:08:49,796
I don’t want it to happen again.

915
01:08:51,214 --> 01:08:54,334
I think you’re being paranoid.

916
01:08:55,979 --> 01:09:02,684
I think you should forget all those bad things that happened to you and enjoy the present moment.

917
01:09:03,796 --> 01:09:04,574
Got it?

918
01:09:07,074 --> 01:09:08,699
I don’t know.

919
01:09:11,088 --> 01:09:12,894
Since I met Phaya again,

920
01:09:13,968 --> 01:09:17,374
I stared to see things.

921
01:09:18,219 --> 01:09:23,408
It’s a vision or a sign about something that will occur in the future.

922
01:09:24,184 --> 01:09:28,688
As if I’m supposed to know when he’s in danger.

923
01:09:30,034 --> 01:09:32,162
- So that I can... / - Can what?

924
01:09:34,756 --> 01:09:35,991
So that I can protect him.

925
01:09:36,779 --> 01:09:40,834
Geez, that sounds like you’ve been cursed.

926
01:09:44,231 --> 01:09:46,688
That’s what I thought so.

927
01:09:53,654 --> 01:09:57,019
Someone wants me to see those visions...

928
01:09:57,991 --> 01:09:59,579
for some unexplainable reasons.

929
01:10:18,231 --> 01:10:21,554
Come on, drink up. Stop thinking too much about it.

930
01:10:30,311 --> 01:10:32,734
- Are you serious?
- P'Yai

931
01:10:36,524 --> 01:10:40,939
Please protect your son.

932
01:10:41,659 --> 01:10:44,002
Don’t let anything bad happen to both of them.

933
01:10:45,088 --> 01:10:47,354
Don’t let what the Abbot has predicted come true.

934
01:11:16,196 --> 01:11:18,802
Hey, are you still up?

935
01:11:20,916 --> 01:11:25,122
A new hut is easier to live than an old castle.

936
01:11:27,434 --> 01:11:30,734
It’s actually ‘a happy hut is better than a gloomy castle.’

937
01:11:31,654 --> 01:11:37,374
I was just kidding. I’m thinking about something.

938
01:11:39,579 --> 01:11:40,596
About what?

939
01:11:43,494 --> 01:11:48,734
I came here because I wanted to find out more about the Naga.

940
01:11:49,488 --> 01:11:50,916
Whether it’s true or not.

941
01:11:52,094 --> 01:11:57,034
About those legends I read from the books, or even about the Naga fireballs.

942
01:11:59,874 --> 01:12:02,996
Do what you believe. Believe in what you do.
(A famous saying from the movie, ‘Mekhong Full Moon Party’)

943
01:12:04,554 --> 01:12:10,054
I watched that movie for so many times.

944
01:12:10,608 --> 01:12:12,596
And other movies about the Naga too.

945
01:12:14,014 --> 01:12:15,865
The more I kept watching them...

946
01:12:16,882 --> 01:12:20,874
the more I started to feel familiar with those stories.

947
01:12:22,844 --> 01:12:24,002
It’s really weird.

948
01:12:24,265 --> 01:12:25,808
I even dreamt about it too.

949
01:12:26,962 --> 01:12:29,099
And drew that picture in your diary.

950
01:12:29,534 --> 01:12:31,914
And believed that I were that girl you drew, right?

951
01:12:32,694 --> 01:12:42,224
It’s not like that. I just feel something every time I get near you.

952
01:12:45,384 --> 01:12:49,099
You mean, as if we’ve met long before we did at the traning camp?

953
01:12:51,682 --> 01:12:54,594
Long before you had saved my life when I was drowning.

954
01:12:56,196 --> 01:13:03,644
I feel as if we have met long before that.

955
01:13:07,259 --> 01:13:09,796
Did you use this kind of story to hit on the girls in France?

956
01:13:11,785 --> 01:13:13,099
Merci Beaucoup. (Thank you in French)

957
01:13:13,545 --> 01:13:15,625
I didn’t use it with every girl that I try to hit on.

958
01:13:15,888 --> 01:13:18,274
I only use it with someone that I really like.

959
01:13:18,882 --> 01:13:19,934
And that someone is you.

960
01:13:23,431 --> 01:13:24,814
You evil jellyfish.

961
01:13:25,248 --> 01:13:26,516
Go get some sleep.

962
01:13:37,694 --> 01:13:40,985
French people do this to say hi and goodbye.

963
01:13:42,985 --> 01:13:45,474
I got it. Can I go to sleep now?

964
01:13:59,534 --> 01:14:02,848
And this is called a ‘goodnight kiss’.

965
01:14:06,505 --> 01:14:07,431
I’m off to bed.

966
01:14:09,019 --> 01:14:10,105
(Yawning)

967
01:15:18,699 --> 01:15:19,968
(Phone buzzing)

968
01:15:20,631 --> 01:15:21,964
(Phone buzzing)

969
01:15:22,734 --> 01:15:23,705
(Phone buzzing)

970
01:15:37,034 --> 01:15:39,154
(On phone screen)
Evil Jellyfish

971
01:15:43,434 --> 01:15:45,945
If you love him, just let him know.

972
01:15:46,044 --> 01:15:48,368
Tell him how you feel.

973
01:15:48,944 --> 01:15:55,254
I don’t want those around me to be in danger.

974
01:15:56,642 --> 01:16:00,551
Geez, stop blaming yourself.

975
01:16:46,504 --> 01:16:50,196
Hey, I gave you a call so many times after we came back from Nong kai,

976
01:16:50,219 --> 01:16:51,922
why didn’t  you answer them?

977
01:16:53,636 --> 01:16:55,191
Nothing serious.

978
01:16:57,065 --> 01:16:58,128
Just too lazy to take the call.

979
01:17:01,682 --> 01:17:03,362
Are you avoiding me?

980
01:17:05,705 --> 01:17:07,431
Why would I do that?

981
01:17:12,802 --> 01:17:13,922
What the fuck?

982
01:17:15,659 --> 01:17:17,328
Hang on.

983
01:17:22,654 --> 01:17:23,922
Why are you blocking my way?

984
01:17:25,168 --> 01:17:26,391
Do you want to get hurt?

985
01:17:29,514 --> 01:17:31,854
Yes, I want to get hurt.

986
01:17:32,094 --> 01:17:33,554
I want to get hurt so badly.

987
01:17:34,231 --> 01:17:37,474
So, can you tell me now why you’re avoiding me?

988
01:17:38,791 --> 01:17:40,859
I’m not avoiding you.

989
01:17:42,756 --> 01:17:43,625
Fine.

990
01:17:44,894 --> 01:17:45,774
Let’s do this.

991
01:17:48,939 --> 01:17:50,928
Let’s have a match. If I win,

992
01:17:52,871 --> 01:17:57,154
you must admit that you’re avoiding me.

993
01:18:01,008 --> 01:18:04,754
- Okay? / - Do you really think you can beat me?

994
01:18:08,345 --> 01:18:09,434
Do you want to try?

995
01:18:11,305 --> 01:18:12,374
I’m going to kick your ass.

996
01:18:22,231 --> 01:18:24,231
- Ready? / - Bring it on.

997
01:19:00,162 --> 01:19:00,882
How does it feel?

998
01:19:25,404 --> 01:19:27,042
- Let me go!
- Do you give in now?

999
01:19:27,351 --> 01:19:28,425
I won.

1000
01:19:29,202 --> 01:19:30,482
- One... / - Let me go!

1001
01:19:31,042 --> 01:19:32,985
- Get off me! / - Two...

1002
01:19:33,636 --> 01:19:34,505
Three...

1003
01:19:35,488 --> 01:19:36,174
Four...

1004
01:19:36,882 --> 01:19:37,674
Five...

1005
01:19:38,345 --> 01:19:40,054
Six, Seven...

1006
01:19:40,054 --> 01:19:42,322
- Eight, Nine...
- Okay, you won!

1007
01:19:42,334 --> 01:19:43,156
you won!

1008
01:19:47,488 --> 01:19:48,368
You lost.

1009
01:19:49,194 --> 01:19:51,419
So, next time when I give you a call...

1010
01:19:51,796 --> 01:19:53,716
you have to answer it. Okay?

1011
01:19:54,871 --> 01:19:55,922
Bolster.

1012
01:19:57,394 --> 01:19:59,434
- Got it?
- Yeah.

1013
01:20:02,688 --> 01:20:04,288
You’re a good boy.

1014
01:20:19,888 --> 01:20:22,082
You’ll meet the leader of Unit 1 today.

1015
01:20:22,322 --> 01:20:24,905
This person will supervise the investigations under your team.

1016
01:20:26,802 --> 01:20:28,894
Is it a he or a she?

1017
01:20:29,545 --> 01:20:33,264
This morning, I saw that the leader of Unit 3...

1018
01:20:33,654 --> 01:20:36,345
is a woman.  She looks so cool.

1019
01:20:37,088 --> 01:20:38,939
You guys are considered very lucky.

1020
01:20:39,008 --> 01:20:40,619
Because your team leader is very experienced.

1021
01:20:40,802 --> 01:20:42,562
Never failed to arrest the criminals in every case.

1022
01:20:42,939 --> 01:20:45,568
Is that why we are Unit 1?

1023
01:20:46,391 --> 01:20:50,274
Yes. There he is, your team leader.

1024
01:21:06,779 --> 01:21:08,391
Attention!

1025
01:21:11,774 --> 01:21:12,608
Inspector.

1026
01:21:15,842 --> 01:21:17,408
Nice to meet you all.

1027
01:21:18,322 --> 01:21:22,734
I’m Police Major Akkanee Assawawaisoon, your team leader.

1028
01:21:23,556 --> 01:21:27,088
Shit, we’re so doomed.

1029
01:21:27,814 --> 01:21:33,214
You didn’t mention anything about being our team leader when we parted, Captain. I mean Inspector.

1030
01:21:35,819 --> 01:21:40,214
If I had mentioned it earlier, I wouldn’t have been able to find out whether you’d be true to your words about your determination...

1031
01:21:40,391 --> 01:21:43,054
when you told me on the last day of the training.

1032
01:21:49,591 --> 01:21:51,522
I can still remember it word by word.

1033
01:21:54,294 --> 01:21:56,025
What did I say to him?

1034
01:21:57,514 --> 01:21:59,579
You gave him an earful.

1035
01:21:59,574 --> 01:22:01,419
Shit.

1036
01:22:01,556 --> 01:22:04,288
Please keep in mind...

1037
01:22:04,494 --> 01:22:05,922
that this is a real workplace.

1038
01:22:06,334 --> 01:22:07,671
You’re no longer at the traning camp.

1039
01:22:08,779 --> 01:22:10,996
I only have three simple rules if we’re going to work together.

1040
01:22:11,636 --> 01:22:14,688
First is teamwork.

1041
01:22:15,568 --> 01:22:17,442
There’ll be no solo investigation.

1042
01:22:17,434 --> 01:22:19,179
Or doing anything without permission or approval from others.

1043
01:22:20,745 --> 01:22:25,234
Second, the supervisor’s order is considered final...

